mas H. Neill]]\n|\n* [[7th Maine Volunteer Infantry Regiment|7th Maine]] (6 companies): Ltc [[Seldon Connor]]\n* [[33rd New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|33rd New York]] (detachment): Cpt Henry J. Gifford\n* [[43rd New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|43rd New York]]: Ltc John Wilson\n* [[49th New York Volunteer Infantry|49th New York]]: Col [[Daniel D. Bidwell]]\n* [[77th New York Volunteer Infantry|77th New York]]: Ltc Winsor B. French\n* [[61st Pennsylvania Infantry|61st Pennsylvania]]: Ltc George F. Smith\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |\nThird Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMG [[John Newton (engineer)|John Newton]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Frank Wheaton]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Alexander Shaler]]\n|\n* [[65th New York Volunteer Infantry|65th New York]]: Col [[Joseph E. Hamblin]]\n* [[67th New York Infantry|67th New York]]: Col Nelson Cross\n* [[122nd New York Volunteer Infantry|122nd New York]]: Col [[Silas Titus]]\n* [[23rd Pennsylvania Volunteer Infantry|23rd Pennsylvania]]: Ltc John F. Glenn\n* [[82nd Pennsylvania Infantry|82nd Pennsylvania]]: Col Isaac C. Bassett\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Henry L. Eustis]]\n|\n* [[7th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|7th Massachusetts]]: Ltc Franklin P. Harlow\n* [[10th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|10th Massachusetts]]: Ltc Joseph B. Parsons\n* [[37th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|37th Massachusetts]]: Col [[Oliver Edwards]]\n* [[2nd Rhode Island Infantry|2nd Rhode Island]]: Col Horatio Rogers, Jr.\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade <ref>The [[102nd Pennsylvania Infantry]] guarded the wagon trains at Westminster, and was not engaged in the battle. However, a detachment of 103 men commanded by Lt Robert W. Lyon was sent as a guard with a supply train and placed on defensive line north of Round Top.</ref>\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Frank Wheaton]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol David J. Nevin\n|\n* [[Anderson Zouaves|62nd New York]]: Col [[David J. Nevin]], Ltc Theodore B. H