fennig]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[George von Amsberg]]\n|\n* [[82nd Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|82nd Illinois]]: Ltc [[Edward S. Salomon]]\n* [[45th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|45th New York]]: Col [[George von Amsberg]], Ltc Adolphus Dobke ('''w''')\n* [[157th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|157th New York]]: Col Philip P. Brown, Jr. ('''w'''), Ltc George Arrowsmith ('''k''')\n* [[61st Ohio Infantry|61st Ohio]]: Col Stephen J. McGroarty, Ltc William H. H. Brown\n* [[74th Pennsylvania Infantry|74th Pennsylvania]]: Col Adolph von Hartung ('''w'''), Ltc Alexander von Mitzel ('''c'''), Cpt Henry Krauseneck\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Wlodzimierz Krzyzanowski|Wladimir Krzyzanowski]]\n|\n* [[58th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|58th New York]]: Ltc August Otto ('''w'''), Cpt Emil Koenig\n* [[119th New York Volunteer Infantry|119th New York]]: Col John T. Lockman ('''w'''), Ltc Edward F. Lloyd\n* [[82nd Ohio Infantry|82nd Ohio]]: Col [[James S. Robinson]] ('''w'''), Ltc David Thomson\n* [[75th Pennsylvania Volunteer Infantry|75th Pennsylvania]]: Col Francis Mahler ('''mw'''), Maj August Ledig\n* [[26th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|26th Wisconsin]]: Ltc Hans Boebel ('''w'''), Maj [[Henry Baetz]] ('''w'''), Cpt John W. Fuchs\n|-\n|\n| Artillery Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMaj [[Thomas W. Osborn]]\n|\n* 1st New York Light, Battery I: Cpt Michael Wiedrich\n* New York Light, 13th Battery: Lt William Wheeler\n* [[Battery I, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light, Battery I]]: Cpt [[Hubert Dilger]]\n* [[Battery K, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light, Battery K]]: Cpt Lewis Heckman\n* [[4th U.S. Artillery, Battery G|4th United States, Battery G]]: Lt Bayard Wilkeson ('''mw'''), Lt Eugene A. Bancroft\n|}\n\n===[[XII Corps (Union Army)|XII Corps]]===\nMG [[Henry Slocum|Henry W. Slocum]] <ref>Exercised command of the right wing of the army during a part of the battle. But see Slocum to Meade, [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu