ffett\n* [[104th New York Volunteer Infantry|104th New York]]: Col Gilbert G. Prey, Ltc Henry Tuthill ('''w''')\n* [[107th Pennsylvania Infantry|107th Pennsylvania]]: Ltc James McThomson ('''w''', July 1), Cpt Emanuel D. Roath\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Henry Baxter]]\n|\n* [[12th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|12th Massachusetts]]: Col [[James L. Bates]] ('''w'''), Ltc David Allen, Jr.\n* [[83rd New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|83rd New York (9th Militia)]]: Ltc Joseph A. Moesch\n* [[97th New York Volunteer Infantry|97th New York]]: Col Charles Wheelock ('''w & c''', July 1), Ltc John P. Spofford ('''c''') Maj Charles B. Northrup\n* [[11th Pennsylvania Infantry|11th Pennsylvania]]:<ref>transferred, in afternoon of July 1, to the First Brigade</ref> Col Richard Coulter, Cpt Benjamin F. Haines ('''w'''), Cpt John B. Overmyer\n* [[88th Pennsylvania Infantry|88th Pennsylvania]]: Maj Benezet F. Foust ('''w''', July 1), Cpt Edmund A. Mass ('''c'''), Cpt Henry Whiteside\n* [[90th Pennsylvania Volunteer Infantry|90th Pennsylvania]]: Col Peter Lyle,<ref>temporarily transferred to the First Brigade</ref> Maj Alfred J. Sellers\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |\nThird Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMG [[Abner Doubleday]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Thomas A. Rowley]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMG Abner Doubleday\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Chapman Biddle]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG Thomas A. Rowley ('''w''')\n|\n* [[80th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|80th New York (20th Militia)]]: Col Theodore B. Gates, Maj Walter A. Van Rensselaer ('''w''')\n* [[121st Pennsylvania Infantry|121st Pennsylvania]]: Col Chapman Biddle, Maj [[Alexander Biddle]]\n* [[142nd Pennsylvania Infantry|142nd Pennsylvania]]: Col Robert P. Cummins ('''mw'''), Ltc Alfred B. McCalmont, Maj Horatio N. Warren\n* [[151st Pennsylvania Infantry|151st Pennsylvania]]: Ltc [[George F. McFarland]] ('''w'''), Cpt Walter L. Owens, Col Harrison Allen\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Roy Stone]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Langhorne Wister]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Edmund L. Dana\n|\n* [[143rd Pennsylvania Infantry|143rd Pennsylvania]]: Col Edmund L. Dana, Ltc John D. Musser ('''w''')\n* [[149th Pennsylvania Infantry|149th Pennsylvania]]: Ltc Walton Dwight ('''w'''), Cpt James Glenn\n* [[150th Pennsylvania Infantry|150th Pennsylvania]]: Col Langhorne Wister, Ltc [[Henry S. Huidekoper]] ('''w'''), Maj Thomas Chamberlin ('''w'''), Cpt Cornelius C. Widdis ('''c'''), Cpt George W. Jones\n|-\n| [[2nd Vermont Brigade|3rd Brigade]] <ref>arrived on the evening of July 1 and did not take part on the first day of the battle [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0043&node=waro0043%3A8&frm=frameset&view=image&seq=368]; [[12th Vermont Infantry|12th Vermont]] and [[15th Vermont Infantry|15th Vermont]] were detached as train guard</ref>\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[George J. Stannard]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Francis V. Randall\n|\n* [[13th Vermont Infantry|13th Vermont]]: Col Francis V. Randall, Ltc William D. Munson ('''w'''), Maj Joseph J. Boynton\n* [[14th Vermont Infantry|14th Vermont]]: Col [[William T. Nichols]], Ltc Charles W. Rose\n* [[16th Vermont Infantry|16th Vermont]]: Col [[Wheelock G. Veazey]], Maj William Rounds\n|-\n|\n| Artillery Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Charles S. Wainwright]]\n|\n* [[2nd Maine Battery|Maine Light, 2nd Battery (B)]]: Cpt James A. Hall\n* [[5th Maine Battery|Maine Light, 5th Battery (E)]]: Cpt [[Greenleaf T. Stevens]] ('''w'''), Lt Edward N. Whittier\n* 1st New York Light, Battery E & [[Battery L, 1st New York Light Artillery|Battery L]]: Cpt Gilbert H. Reynolds ('''w''', July 1), Lt George Breck\n* [[Battery B, 1st Pennsylvania Light Artillery|1st Pennsylvania Light, Battery B]]: Cpt James H. Cooper\n* [[4th U.S. Artillery, Battery B|4th United States, Battery B]]: Lt [[James Stewart (artilleryman)|James Stewart]] ('''w'''), Lt James Davison ('''w''')\n|}\n\n===[[II Corps (Union Army)|II Corps]]===\nMG [[Winfield S. Hancock]]<ref>After the death of General Reynolds, General Hancock was assigned to the command of all troops on the field of battle [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0045&node=waro0045%3A5&frm=frameset&view=image&seq=463], relieving General Howard, who had succeeded General Reynolds. General Gibbon, of the Second Division, assumed command of the corps. These assignments terminated on the evening of July 1. Similar changes in commanders occurred during the battle of the 2nd, when General Hancock was put in command of the Third Corps in addition to that of his own. He was wounded on the 3rd, and Brigadier General William Hays [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0045&node=waro0045%3A5&frm=frameset&view=image&seq=505] was assigned to the command of the corps.</ref> ('''w''')\n<br>\nBG [[John Gibbon]]\n<br>\nBG [[William Hays (general)|William Hays]]\n<br>\nGeneral Headquarters:\n* 6th New York Cavalry, Companies D and K: Cpt Riley Johnson (Escort)\n* [[53rd Pennsylvania Infantry]] , Companies A, B and K: Maj Octavus Bull (Provost Marshal 2nd Corps) <ref>under the command of General Patrick (Provost Marshal General of the Army) during the battle [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0043&node=waro0043%3A8&frm=frameset&view=image&seq=396]</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Division\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Brigade\n! Regiments and Others\n|-\n| rowspan=4 |\nFirst Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[John C. Caldwell]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Edward E. Cross]] ('''mw''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[H. Boyd McKeen]]\n|\n* [[5th New Hampshire Volunteer Infantry|5th New Hampshire]]: Ltc Charles E. Hapgood, Maj Richard E. Cross\n* [[61st New York Volunteer Infantry|61st New York]]: Ltc [[K. Oscar Broady]]\n* [[81st Pennsylvania Infantry|81st Pennsylvania]]: Col Henry Boyd McKeen, Ltc Amos Stroh\n* [[148th Pennsylvania Infantry|148th Pennsylvania]]: Col H. Boyd McKeen,<ref>Col McKeen was placed in temporary command of the 148th Pennsylvania Infantry because Colonel James Addams Beaver was ill. Col Edward E. Cross believed that Ltc McFarlane was too inexperienced to lead the regiment.</ref> Ltc Robert McFarlane, Maj Robert H. Foster\n|-\n| [[Irish Brigade (US)|2nd Brigade]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Patrick Kelly (Colonel)|Patrick Kelly]]\n|\n* [[28th Massachusetts Infantry regiment|28th Massachusetts]]: Col Richard Byrnes\n* [[63rd New York Infantry]] (2 companies): Ltc Richard C. Bentley ('''w'''), Cpt Thomas Touhy\n* [[U.S. 69th Infantry Regiment|69th New York]] (2 companies): Cpt Richard Moroney ('''w'''), Lt James J. Smith\n* [[88th New York Infantry]] (2 companies): Cpt Denis F. Burke\n* [[116th Pennsylvania Infantry|116th Pennsylvania]] (4 companies): Maj [[St. Clair Augustine Mulholland|St. Clair A. Mulholland]]\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Samuel K. Zook]] ('''mw''' July 2)\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nLtc Charles G. Freudenberg ('''w''' July 2)\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Richard P. Roberts ('''k''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nLtc John Fraser\n|\n* [[52nd New York Volunteer Infantry|52nd New York]]: Ltc Charles G. Freudenberg ('''w''' July 2), Maj Edward Venuti ('''k'''), Cpt William Scherrer\n* [[57th New York Volunteer Infantry|57th New York]]: Ltc Alford B. Chapman\n* [[66th New York Volunteer Infantry|66th New York]]: Col Orlando H. Morris ('''w'''), Ltc John S. Hammell ('''w'''), Maj Peter A. Nelson\n* [[140th Pennsylvania Volunteer Infantry|140th Pennsylvania]]: Col Richard P. Roberts, Ltc John Fraser, Maj Thomas Rodgers\n|-\n| 4th Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[John R. Brooke]] ('''w''')\n|\n* [[27th Connecticut Infantry Regiment|27th Connecticut]] (2 companies): Ltc Henry C. Merwin ('''k'''), Maj James H. Coburn\n* [[2nd Delaware Volunteer Infantry|2nd Delaware]]: Col William P. Bailey ('''w''' July 2), Ltc David L. Stricker ('''w''' July 2), Cpt Charles H. Christman\n* [[64th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|64th New York]]: Col Daniel G. Bingham ('''w'''), Maj Leman W. Bradley ('''w''')\n* [[53rd Pennsylvania Infantry|53rd Pennsylvania]]: Ltc Richards McMichael\n* [[145th Pennsylvania Infantry|145th Pennsylvania]] (7 companies): Col Hiram Loomis Brown ('''w''' July 2), Cpt John W. Reynolds ('''w''' July 2), Cpt Moses W. Oliver\n|-\n| rowspan=4 |\nSecond Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[John Gibbon]] ('''w''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[William Harrow]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[William Harrow]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Francis E. Heath ('''w''')\n|\n* [[19th Maine Volunteer Infantry Regiment|19th Maine]]: Col Francis E. Heath, Ltc Henry W. Cunningham\n* [[15th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|15th Massachusetts]]: Col [[George Hull Ward|George H. Ward]] ('''mw'''), Ltc George C. Joslin, Maj Isaac H. Hooper\n* [[1st Minnesota Volunteer Infantry|1st Minnesota]]:<ref>2nd Company Minnesota Sharpshooters attached</ref> Col [[William Colvill (colonel)|William Colvill, Jr.]] ('''w'''), Cpt Nathan S. Messick ('''k'''), Cpt Henry C. Coates\n* [[82nd New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|82nd New York (2nd Militia)]]: Ltc James Huston ('''mw'''), Maj Thomas W. Baird ('''w'''),  Cpt John Darrow\n|-\n| [[Philadelphia Brigade|2nd Brigade]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Alexander S. Webb]] ('''w''')\n|\n* [[69th Pennsylvania Infantry|69th Pennsylvania]]: Col Dennis O'Kane ('''mw'''), Ltc Martin Tschudy ('''k'''), Maj James M. Duffy ('''w'''), Cpt William Davis\n* [[71st Pennsylvania Volunteers|71st Pennsylvania]]: Col Richard P. Smith, Ltc [[Charles Kochersperger]]\n* [[72nd Pennsylvania Infantry|72nd Pennsylvania]]: Col [[De Witt C. Baxter]] ('''w'''), Ltc Theodore Hesser, Maj Samuel Roberts\n* [[106th Pennsylvania Infantry|106th Pennsylvania]]: Ltc Willi