ine]]: Col Moses B. Lakeman, Maj Samuel P. Lee ('''w''')\n* [[4th Maine Volunteer Infantry Regiment|4th Maine]]: Col Elijah Walker ('''w'''), Maj Ebenezer Whitcomb ('''mw'''), Cpt Edwin Libby\n* [[86th New York Volunteer Infantry|86th New York]]: Ltc Benjamin L. Higgins ('''w''', July 2), Maj Jacob A. Lansing\n* [[124th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|124th New York]]: Col [[Augustus van Horne Ellis|Augustus van H. Ellis]] ('''k'''), Ltc Francis M. Cummins ('''w'''), Maj James Cromwell ('''k''')\n* [[99th Pennsylvania Infantry|99th Pennsylvania]]: Maj John W. Moore ('''w'''), Cpt Peter Fritz, Jr.<ref>Cpt Fritz commanded the regiment after Maj Moore was wounded; Maj Moore returned to command on July 3</ref>\n* [[1st United States Volunteer Sharpshooter Regiment|1st United States Sharpshooters]]: Col [[Hiram Berdan]], Ltc Casper Trepp\n* [[2nd United States Volunteer Sharpshooter Regiment|2nd United States Sharpshooters]] (8 companies): Maj Homer R. Stoughton\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[R\u00e9gis de Trobriand|P. R\u00e9gis de Trobriand]]\n|\n* [[17th Maine Volunteer Infantry Regiment|17th Maine]]: Ltc Charles B. Merrill, Maj George W. West\n* [[3rd Michigan Volunteer Infantry Regiment|3rd Michigan]]: Col Byron R. Pierce ('''w'''), Ltc Edwin S. Pierce, Maj Moses B. Houghton\n* [[5th Michigan Volunteer Infantry Regiment|5th Michigan]]: Ltc John Pulford ('''w'''), Maj Salmon S. Matthews ('''w''')\n* [[40th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|40th New York]]: Col Thomas W. Egan ('''w'''), Ltc Augustus J. Warner ('''w''')\n* [[110th Pennsylvania Infantry|110th Pennsylvania]] (6 companies): Ltc David M. Jones ('''w''' July 2), Maj Isaac Rogers\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |\nSecond Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Andrew A. Humphreys]]\n| 1st Brigade <ref>The [[84th Pennsylvania Infantry|84th Pennsylvania]] guarded the corps trains, and was not engaged in the battle.</ref>\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Joseph B. Carr]] ('''w''')\n|\n* [[1st Regiment Massa