rmont Brigade|2nd Brigade]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Lewis A. Grant]]\n|\n* [[2nd Vermont Infantry|2nd Vermont]]: Col James H. Walbridge\n* [[3rd Vermont Infantry|3rd Vermont]]: Col [[Thomas O. Seaver]]\n* [[4th Vermont Infantry|4th Vermont]]: Col [[Charles B. Stoughton]]\n* [[5th Vermont Infantry|5th Vermont]]: Ltc John R. Lewis\n* [[6th Vermont Infantry|6th Vermont]]: Col Elisha L. Barney\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Thomas H. Neill]]\n|\n* [[7th Maine Volunteer Infantry Regiment|7th Maine]] (6 companies): Ltc [[Seldon Connor]]\n* [[33rd New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|33rd New York]] (detachment): Cpt Henry J. Gifford\n* [[43rd New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|43rd New York]]: Ltc John Wilson\n* [[49th New York Volunteer Infantry|49th New York]]: Col [[Daniel D. Bidwell]]\n* [[77th New York Volunteer Infantry|77th New York]]: Ltc Winsor B. French\n* [[61st Pennsylvania Infantry|61st Pennsylvania]]: Ltc George F. Smith\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |\nThird Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMG [[John Newton (engineer)|John Newton]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Frank Wheaton]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Alexander Shaler]]\n|\n* [[65th New York Volunteer Infantry|65th New York]]: Col [[Joseph E. Hamblin]]\n* [[67th New York Infantry|67th New York]]: Col Nelson Cross\n* [[122nd New York Volunteer Infantry|122nd New York]]: Col [[Silas Titus]]\n* [[23rd Pennsylvania Volunteer Infantry|23rd Pennsylvania]]: Ltc John F. Glenn\n* [[82nd Pennsylvania Infantry|82nd Pennsylvania]]: Col Isaac C. Bassett\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Henry L. Eustis]]\n|\n* [[7th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|7th Massachusetts]]: Ltc Franklin P. Harlow\n* [[10th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|10th Massachusetts]]: Ltc Joseph B. Parsons\n* [[37th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|37th Massachusetts]]: Col [[Oliver Edwards]]\n* [[2nd Rhode Island Infantry|2nd Rhode Island]]: Col Horatio Rogers, Jr.\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade <ref>The [[102nd Pennsylvania Infantry]] guarded the wagon trains at Westminster, and was not engaged in the battle. However, a detachment of 103 men commanded by Lt Robert W. Lyon was sent as a guard with a supply train and placed on defensive line north of Round Top.</ref>\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Frank Wheaton]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol David J. Nevin\n|\n* [[Anderson Zouaves|62nd New York]]: Col [[David J. Nevin]], Ltc Theodore B. Hamilton\n* [[93rd Pennsylvania Infantry|93rd Pennsylvania]]: Maj John I. Nevin\n* [[98th Pennsylvania Infantry|98th Pennsylvania]]: Maj John B. Kohler\n* [[139th Pennsylvania Infantry|139th Pennsylvania]]: Col Frederick H. Collier ('''w'''), Ltc William H. Moody\n|-\n|\n| Artillery Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Charles H. Tompkins]]\n|\n* Massachusetts Light, 1st Battery (A): Cpt William H. McCartney\n* New York Light, 1st Battery: Cpt [[Andrew Cowan (artillerist)|Andrew Cowan]]\n* [[3rd New York Independent Light Artillery|New York Light, 3rd Battery]]: Cpt [[William A. Harn]]\n* [[Battery C, 1st Rhode Island Light Artillery|1st Rhode Island Light, Battery C]]: Cpt Richard Waterman\n* [[Battery G, 1st Rhode Island Light Artillery|1st Rhode Island Light, Battery G]]: Cpt George W. Adams\n* 2nd United States, Battery D: Lt [[Edward B. Williston]]\n* [[2nd U.S. Artillery, Battery G|2nd United States, Battery G]]: Lt John H. Butler\n* [[5th Field Artillery Regiment (United States)|5th United States]], Battery F: Lt Leonard Martin\n|}\n\n===[[XI Corps (Union Army)|XI Corps]]===\nMG [[Oliver O. Howard]] <ref>During the interval between the death of General Reynolds and the arrival of General Hancock on the afternoon of July 1, all the troops on the field of battle were commanded by General Howard, General Schurz taking command of the Eleventh Corps, and General Schimmelfennig of the Third Division</ref>\n<br>\nMG [[Carl Schurz]]\n\nGeneral Headquarters:\n* 1st Indiana Cavalry, Companies I and K: Cpt Abram Sharra\n* 8th New York Infantry (1 company): Lt Hermann Foerster\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Division\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Brigade\n! Regiments and Others\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |\nFirst Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Francis C. Barlow]] ('''w&c''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Adelbert Ames]]\n|\n1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Leopold von Gilsa]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\n|\n* [[41st New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|41st New York]] (9 companies): Ltc Detleo von Einsiedel\n* [[54th New York Volunteer Infantry|54th New York]]: Maj Stephen Kovacs ('''c'''), Lt Ernst Both\n* [[68th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|68th New York]]: Col Gotthilf Bourry\n* 153rd Pennsylvania: Maj John F. Frueauff\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Adelbert Ames]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Andrew L. Harris]]\n|\n* [[17th Connecticut Infantry Regiment|17th Connecticut]]: Ltc Douglas Fowler ('''k''' July 1), Maj Allen G. Brady ('''w''' July 2)\n* [[25th Ohio Infantry|25th Ohio]]: Ltc Jeremiah Williams ('''c'''), Cpt Nathaniel J. Manning ('''w'''), Lt William Maloney ('''w'''), Lt Israel White\n* [[75th Ohio Infantry|75th Ohio]]: Col [[Andrew L. Harris]], Cpt George B. Fox\n* [[107th Ohio Infantry|107th Ohio]]: Col Seraphim Meyer ('''w'''), Cpt John M. Lutz\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |\nSecond Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Adolph von Steinwehr]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Charles Coster|Charles R. Coster]]\n|\n* [[134th New York Volunteer Infantry|134th New York]]: Ltc Allan H. Jackson ('''c'''), Maj George W. B. Seeley\n* [[154th New York Volunteer Infantry|154th New York]]: Ltc Daniel B. Allen, Maj Lewis D. Warner\n* [[27th Pennsylvania Infantry|27th Pennsylvania]]: Ltc Lorenz Cantador\n* [[73rd Pennsylvania Infantry|73rd Pennsylvania]]: Cpt Daniel F. Kelley\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Orland Smith]]\n|\n* [[33rd Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|33rd Massachusetts]]: Col [[Adin B. Underwood]]\n* [[136th New York Volunteer Infa